race.description: The Gibson Fillies And Mares Bm70 Handicap
race.comment: PIERATA'S GEM (5) was ridden closer to the pace than expected and didn't quite finish the race off over 1400m at the Sunshine Coast a fortnight ago. This is the weakest race she has contested for a while. The Munce go-to man Martin Harley takes over - today must be her day. DAVIKAR (8) made it three wins from six career runs when she was a shade too good for GLASS OF ROSE over this distance at Ipswich last time out. Needs to raise the bar but she gets in well after the claim for Jai Williams who could win on a broomstick at the moment. TEN DEEP (4) sat just off the pace then drove hard late to just arrive in time when resuming over 1200m here recently. Yet to miss the frame in six runs at or around this trip. Can go back-to-back. Distance specialist ARIAT (6) has won two in a two in a row and looks ready to tackle this better race. GLASS OF ROSE (13) returned to form last start behind DAVIKAR and will be peaking at the fourth run back.
